gut
Homonym Number:
Word Class: noun
Sense Number:  1
Definition:[mustering and hunting] a high steep narrow chute between rocks, where sheep or deer can pass [often at the top of a shingle fan and that can fill with fast-moving water.]


Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain: Rural
Region: [none]
See: chute; chimney; staircase
Pronunciation:
